gomodel:SYNGO_4084  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 6A: Overexpression of Cbln2 increased both AMPA (Fig 6A) and NMDA currents (Fig 6B) in the hippocampus.\nFigure B and C: The increased AMPA and NMDA EPSC currents induced by overexpression of Cbln2 were abolished when GluD1 was knocked down indicating that Cbln2 is the endogenous ligand for GluD1 and mediates the transsynaptic effects of GluD1 at CA1 excitatory synapses.\nFigure 7: Overexpression of GluD1 increased AMPA and NMDA EPSC currents. However, this effect was negated in Cbln2 KO mice indicating the specificity of Clbn2 for GluD1.\nFigure 8: GluD1 actions require presynaptic neurexin 1β.\nFigure S6: To exclude off-target effects of the Cbln2 KO, overexpression of Cbln2 in overexpressed GluD1 rescued the Cbln2 KO phenotype.. Experimental description: Cbln2 KO mice were obtained from James I. Morgan's laboratory at St. Jude Children's Hospital, Memphis, TN, and were bred at the University of California, San Francisco. Hippocampal cultured slices are obtained from 6- to 8-d old mice and were further used for electrophysiology." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4084" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

